Literacy Kansas City's mission is to advance literacy among area teens and adults through direct services, advocacy and collaboration. Our vision is literacy for all. Founded in 1985, Literacy Kansas City has grown to become the premiere area agency focused solely on adult literacy instruction through evidence-based adult literacy programming. Literacy Kansas City has touched thousands of adults reading at or below the basic level of literacy- meaning approximately fifth grade- throughout the Kansas City metro.  In addition to providing one to one and small group tutoring to students, Literacy Kansas City has broadened the delivery of our literacy instruction to include innovative classroom-based programs coupled with one-to-one tutoring, culminating in the GEARS (Guided Educational Access to Reading Skills) program in partnership with Penn Valley Community College. The success of this program led to the development of a new project: the Family Literacy Project. For the first time, Literacy Kansas City offers programming with a multi-generational approach to the inter-generational problem of illiteracy that includes classroom, tutoring and family and digital literacy components.In January 2015, Literacy Kansas City will launch the Impact Initiative. This research-driven, community-based literacy effort maximizes organizational efficiency and programmatic effectiveness through strategic barrier elimination, and meets students where they are, both academically and geographically. Through partnerships with the Kansas City Public Library, Mid-Continent Public Library, Connecting for Good, Kansas City Public Schools, Turn the Page KC, Upper Room, LINC, and KC Parks and Recreation, we will establish satellite sites throughout the metro. In addition to our home offices, these sites will be convenient locations for students to access comprehensive, computer-based literacy education that includes balanced literacy instruction, digital literacy, job readiness, ELL, and more.

reStart Inc. is an interfaith ministry with homeless persons committed to providing shelter and supportive services to homeless men, women, youth and families with the goal of helping them move toward independence and self-sufficiency and ending homelessness in our community. Over our more than 30 years of service in the urban core of Kansas City, Missouri, reStart has evolved from a crisis center providing emergency food and shelter for the homeless into a community advocate, seeking to identify and address the numerous and complex factors that contribute to chronic and generational homelessness. While we continue to provide basic essentials (food and shelter) to the most vulnerable members of our community, we have expanded our objectives to include educating and equipping individuals and families to break cyles of poverty and homelessness and to achieve healthy lifestyles, economic stability and permanent housing. We intentionally target programming to homeless children and youth to prevent them from becoming the next generation of homeless adults.

mission:
Our primary mission is to provide rescue and adoption services to homeless companion birds.  We do not turn away birds due to medical needs, and accept transfers of sick and special needs birds from other rescue groups.  We are a no-kill shelter, and birds can live here as long as needed until they find their forever homes.  When possible, we will also help outdoor pet birds such as chickens, ducks, and pigeons, and wild birds that need emergency care.

 

Our mission also includes disaster and hoarding animal rescue and sheltering.  We will travel where needed to assist animals impacted by natural or man-made disasters and help provide care until they can be returned home or placed in safe new homes.
